summary: A portable ANSI C implementation of MurmurHash3_x86_32 (Murmur3A) that provides type definitions and function prototypes for hash computation with support for progressive processing.

logs.message_template: Unable to determine type name for unsigned 32-bit int
logs.reason: This error is triggered during compilation when the preprocessor cannot determine a suitable type to use for a 32-bit unsigned integer based on the available platform types and limits.
logs.resolution: This is a build-time error that indicates the code is being compiled on a platform with unusual integer size definitions. Modify the preprocessor conditions to include support for the target platform's integer types, or define MH_UINT32 manually for the specific platform.
